3. That we ſhould be holy; Ergo, not becauſe we were holy;
and ſo the Apoſtle ſpeaks of faith, God had mercie on me: Vt
fidelis eſſem, not becauſe I was faithfull.

THAT which our Saviour delivered in the former part of the Precedent verſe, That not all that profeſſe Chriſt to be their Lord ſhall be ſaved, is in theſe two verſes confirmed; for a man may have moſt excellent gifts, and in reſpect of his Calling come neer unto Chriſt, be his Vice-gerent, and ſupply his roome, and for all that miſſe heaven. Many will ſay unto me, &c. In which words note;
1. The plea of certaine perſons.
2. Chriſts anſwer; Then will I profeſſe, &c.

I confeſſe I could never approve of thoſe lapwings, which having hopped out of their neſts, with their ſhels on their heads, before they got a feather on their backs: Priuſquam ſacra volumina vel nomine noverint, priuſquam veteris & novi testamenti ſigna not aſque cognoverint, as Nazianzen ſpeaks, having provided themſelves of halfe a dozen Sermons, which they have as good right too, as Paulus in Martiall had to his Verſes;
Carmina Paulus emit, jactat ſua Carmina Paulus;
Nam quod emit poterit dicere jure ſuum.
